The paper deals with domain adaptation in robotic vision, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep learning methods for domain adaptation suggests that the paper could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subcategories. Finally, the use of multiple modalities (RGB and depth) suggests that the paper could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) subcategory.
